UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2427
1 AN ACT relating to juvenile justice.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 15A.066 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) (a) An[No] employee of the Department of Juvenile Justice shall not be required
5 to give personal attendance as a witness in any civil action[suit] arising out of
6 or related to his or her employment[,] outside[out of] the county of that
7 employee's assigned work station except as provided in subsection (2) of this
8 section.[, but ]
9 (b) This subsection shall not preclude taking his or her testimony by deposition
10 or as otherwise provided in the Rules of Civil Procedure[ shall be taken] in
11 lieu of personal attendance.[thereof; however, ]
12 (2) If the court in which the civil action is pending finds that the witness is a necessary
13 witness for trial, that court may order the personal attendance of the witness at trial.
